  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "`abi.encodePacked` was introduced in 0.4.22 as a backwards compatibility measure for the irregular \"packed\" encoding.\r\n\r\nSince then we have introduced `bytes.concat` (#10903) and learned that most projects (rightly) do not rely on the packed encoding, but only concatenation. I suggest we drop `abi.encodePacked` in the next breaking release.\r\n\r\n(We could consider introducing a message with #11508 if we want to test the waters ðŸ˜… , but would rather refrain from this.)",
